column35: MyKore Essentials
column36:
#INGREDIENTS:
1 avocado
1 cup cooked #sweetpotato purée
½ cup applesauce
¼–½ cup #honey
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
4 eggs
¼ cup #coconut flour
2 tablespoons arrowroot powder
½ cup cacao powder
½ teaspoon sea salt
1 teaspoon baking soda

For the frosting:
¼ cup honey
½ cup sprouted #almond butter
¼ cup cacao powder
½ cup coconut milk
sea salt

#DIRECTIONS:
Preheat your oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit.
Prepare an 8x8 baking pan by greasing it with coconut oil and lining with parchment paper.
Use a mixer to combine the avocado, sweet potato, applesauce, honey and vanilla in a medium bowl. Once creamy, add the cacao powder.
Slowly add the eggs one at a time.
Combine the coconut flour, arrowroot flour, salt and baking soda in a separate bowl.
Next, combine both mixtures until smooth.
Transfer to the batter to the greased pan. Bake for 25–35 minutes.
While baking, combine the frosting ingredients in a bowl. Mix until creamy and smooth.
When the brownies are done, allow them to cool completely before frosting.
Enjoy!

column31: A lot of people who have never questioned vaccines before are suddenly asking because of the possibility of a forced COVID vaccine. They don't see the point in mandating a vaccine for an illness with a high survival rate. Well...we've got news for you! The media has been trying to make childhood illnesses sound terrifying by purposely telling the stories of the worst outcomes. But when we look at their actual mortality rates vs. COVID, we see a different picture..... The note on "lab confirmed cases" is because with some illnesses, they circulate in the community a lot, and only a small fraction of people go to the doctor to get tested. With measles, it was about 400,000 confirmed cases per year, but pre-vaccine, it was really around 4 million in total (which would make the mortality rate only 0.001%). With COVID, no one really knows how many asymptomatic or mild cases there really are, but it's assumed to be much higher than the confirmed cases. This could drop the overall mortality rate to 0.3%, and childhood mortality is as low as 0% in some areas. Basically...this "pandemic" has allowed us to gain some perspective. How do you feel about this?

column31: There is a new company called Biomilq, who is harvesting human mammary cells to produce breast milk in a lab -- intending to replace formula. We have strongly mixed feelings about this. On one hand, we want better options for babies whose mothers cannot or do not breastfeed. All babies should have access to human milk, as it is species-specific and provides optimal nutrition in a way that current formulas simply cannot. On the other hand... How close will it be to breast milk? What will the long term health outcomes look like? Will there be even less support for breastfeeding than there is now? (People already say formula is "good enough" and shame mothers who breastfeed in public or too long. If an even better substitute existed, would this get worse?) The project has been heavily funded by Bill Gates, the Rockefeller Foundation, and other suspect characters, so there's that consideration too. Breaking News, CA: Robert F. Kennedy Jr. and Colleagues File Lawsuit Against University of California Regents Over New Flu Vaccine Mandate

1. This case challenges the Executive Order issued by former UC System President Janet Napolitano on July 31, 2020, mandating the flu vaccine for all students, faculty, and employees by November 1, 2020 as a condition of continued employment and continued school enrollment for students.[1]

2. There are three reasons why the EO must be struck down. First, it was issued in violation of the UC governance documents and shared governance principles requiring formal consultation with the Faculty Senate.

3. Second, the EO is unconstitutional because it compels the 510,000-member community to vaccinate against the flu, which has no proven benefit against COVID-19. As a result, the actual justification for the flu vaccine mandate boils down to mitigating a possible future shortage of hospital beds, if there is a second wave, and if there is a big seasonal flu outbreak, and if as a result, there would be a shortage of hospital beds.[2]

4. Constitutionally, there are just too many “ifs” to force 510,000 people to sacrifice their rights to personal liberty, privacy and bodily integrity.

5. Further, there is an established medical phenomenon known as viral or vaccine interference, meaning that one vaccine may increase the risk of infection, hospitalization, and death from another vaccine or another virus.

6. Based on observational studies, including one which specifically found that the flu vaccine was associated with a significantly increased risk of contracting common coronaviruses, it is possible that this flu vaccine mandate could cause increased COVID-19 cases, hospitalizations, and deaths – not the reverse.

To continue reading the full complaint, go here: https://rickjaffeesq.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Complaintwithexhibits.pdf

column31: If you go to the CDC website below, you’ll find the following information. 📈 Total COVID-19 deaths as of 8/22/2020: 161,392. 📊 94% of deaths documented as COVID had additional conditions or causes of death. On average, there were 2.6 additional conditions or causes per death. 💡For 6% of the deaths, COVID-19 was the only cause mentioned. 👉🏻 That’s 9,684 deaths. Why does this matter? Did you know that the method for recording cause of death was changed for COVID cases? Typically when a person has documented chronic conditions or comorbidities, the very first health condition that was acquired is listed as the primary cause of death. Not so for COVID... 👁 Watch ➜ https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=twI06UfCk_w&feature=youtu.be&fbclid=IwAR1R3qvVqgXRNLC1hc5-4fR5rbFewZMpscnwDfVk1kRq1CbluQNEdqH51Ek For COVID, “COVID-19” is listed as the primary cause of death regardless of what other chronic conditions the person had, no matter how severe or serious they were. Check the table below. 👇🏻 80% of “COVID” deaths occur in ages 65 and up. This is not unique to COVID. From the CDC: “...it’s estimated that between 70 percent and 85 percent of seasonal flu-related deaths have occurred in people 65 years and older.” ➜ https://www.cdc.gov/flu/highrisk/65over.htm (Average US life expectancy is 78.5 years.) 42% of “COVID” deaths also had influenza or pneumonia listed as a cause of death. 🤔 Also: 5,133 “COVID” deaths also had intentional or unintentional injuries, poisonings, etc. listed as a cause of death... Yet somehow, these made the list for COVID deaths...? What happened? Did someone sustain fatal injuries in a car accident and they were tested for COVID before they died? I mean what on earth does this mean? This was already exposed in an Orlando Florida Fox news investigation, by the way ➜ https://www.facebook.com/100000349373954/posts/3238829442805336/ 😳 All of this sure instills confidence in what’s being reported by the media, doesn’t it? . . column31: A kindergarten student was denied a ride on the school bus for not wearing a mask. 5-year-old Jack, who has autism, is unable to wear a mask for long periods of time. His father called the school district's transportation department prior to this, and was told that students with special needs were not required to wear masks. However, that was not the case. As Jack tried to get on the school bus, the bus driver informed him it was mandatory to wear a mask. His parents tried to explain that they were told he didn't have to wear one. The bus driver called a district staff member who said Jack couldn't ride without a mask. Jack was devastated and confused, and his father ended up driving him to school. This was his first day of kindergarten. Mask mandates have gotten out of hand, with many people who have legitimate exemptions, like Jack, being denied and even bullied. Are you okay with special needs students being treated this way? https://nypost.com/2020/08/27/arizona-boy-with-autism-kicked-off-bus-for-no-mask-parents/?fbclid=IwAR158WRtROc3Vtjl6epYCNceYzZQnBtjVzbLFvsEfGHj8Px3GK-uXU9Xq4c

column31: Health Concerns of Fluoride The chronic toxic effects of fluoride often include dental and skeletal fluorosis, but the biggest concern may be its effects on the brain. The association between excessive ingestion of fluoride and dental mottling (fluorosis) was initially discovered over a century ago by Frederick Sumner McKay a practicing dentist in Colorado Springs area and G. V. Black. Fluoride can cross the blood brain barrier prior to birth and has been reported to affect mental development, learning disorders, and decrease intelligence and hyperactivity in children. In fetal brain, the levels of the neurotransmitters and the number of receptors are also reported to decrease in endemic fluoride areas. The fetal brain is also susceptible to fluoride poisoning. Fluoride effects the fetal brain tissues and results in remark-able neurological damage, neuronal degeneration, and reduced secretion of neurotransmitters such as norepinephrine. In addition, fluoride disrupts the secretion of certain neurotransmitters and nerve cell receptors and results in neural dysplasia. Countries that have synthetic fluoridation added to their water supply, have on average, higher child mortality rates. column31: Lily, an 80 year-old in my group fitness class, would often coo at me “You’re so beautiful.” I believed her 😁 until the day I overheard her telling a rather plain woman that she was beautiful. 🤨 What?!? I felt lied to! And disappointed. I wasn’t truly beautiful, after all. Lily apparently just had the habit of saying this to every. single. person. she came across! 😮 And then it hit me. Lily wasn’t lying. Every single person she met WAS beautiful. 😍 Lily wasn’t blind either; she probably had the clearest vision of all. She saw what too many of us overlooked. Every person we encounter IS beautiful. 🧡 How could I have missed this truth?! Somehow I had let Hollywood’s veneer-capped, airbrushed, artificially-enhanced standards cloud my vision. Forget that. I own it. I had simply been measuring beauty far too superficially. For y-e-a-r-s. And then a second light bulb went off.💡 Lily was THE most beautiful of us all because of her gift of perceiving & appreciating beauty all around her. This was an epiphany for me. See beauty. Welcome beauty. Be beauty. Because you are beautiful. Just as you are. If you don’t believe me, ask Lily. 🥰 🧡🧡🧡 Había una señora de tercera edad, Lily, en mi clase de ejercicio que siempre me decía “Qué bella eres!” Yo con gusto le creía hasta que un día la oí dar el mismo piropo a una mujer muy sencilla y humilde de apariencia (según yo). Me quedé sorprendida y me preguntaba si Lily era sincera o si simplemente le mentía a todo el mundo. 🤨 Luego me di cuenta que ella decía la verdad. Porque sí, cada uno es obra de arte. Bell@. Si no lo vemos así, quizás tengamos un entendimiento superficial de belleza. Por eso les digo hoy: Véan la belleza. Búsquenla. Séanla. Porque sí lo eres. Bell@. 🥰 Y si no me crees, pregúntale a Lily.

column31: Watch out for something called "removal of permissive language" -- we're likely going to see a LOT of this in the fall! This is one way doctors manipulate families into receiving vaccines or other medical procedures they don't really want. Here's what they do: instead of asking if you want it, or providing you with all the info and answering all their questions, they make the assumption that you WILL get it -- because most will give in. "Permissive" language might be: "Hello, Mrs. Y. Today I recommend ____ vaccines. Would you like to receive those? Do you have any questions?" Removal of "permissive language" might be: "Hello, Mrs. Y. It's time for ____ vaccines. I already have them drawn up, so let's get started." The second doesn't leave much room for arguments. It leads most people to think they don't really have a choice. They KNOW most people will give in if they phrase things this way. Is this ethical? We don't think so.

column31: What are you having for dinner? 🥙🍚🍽 If you have nothing on the menu, check out this easy and delicious home-made stuffed mushroom chicken recipe! Ingredients: 4 large chicken breasts, slit to create a pocket 4 tbsp. butter 16 oz. mushrooms 1 small onion, minced 4 – 5 cloves garlic, minced ½ cup white wine 2 oz. Romano cheese, shredded 2 cups gluten-free stuffing mix (or regular bread cubes) 1 tsp. salt Step 1: Carefully cut your chicken breasts through the middle, but not all the way, to create a pocket for your stuffing. If it doesn’t stay all the way closed, and there are holes in it…it will be okay. Set them aside. Step 2: Melt butter in a large skillet on medium heat. Add the chicken, sprinkled with salt and pepper, and cook on each side for about 5 min or until golden brown. It won’t be cooked through, but that’s okay. Transfer chicken to a baking dish, and set aside. Step 3: Add the butter, onion, and mushrooms to the skillet. Cook for about 5 minutes, or until veggies are softened. Preheat oven to 350. Step 4: Add the garlic and cook for another minute. Sprinkle with a pinch of salt. Step 5: Add the wine and stir to get any bits of the bottom of the pan. Step 6: Add the stuffing mix, green onions, and cheese and stir it all together. Step 7: Scoop the stuffing mix into the chicken pockets. Get as much in as you can. Step 8: Bake the chicken for about 25 – 30 min, or until cooked through. Serve immediately, or it can be refrigerated or frozen until later — it reheats well! (I made a bunch and portioned it out for meals later.) Enjoy! https://modernalternativemama.com/2020/04/13/recipe-collection-stuffed-mushroom-chicken/

How To Make #BananaPeelTea:
First, choose your bananas. Look for the ones that are already very ripe. The riper the better. In this state, the peel becomes sweeter and thinner thanks to the ethylene that is produced as they ripen.
.
You can make tea from the peel of a #banana you just ate, or you can use the entire #fruit if you prefer. If you use the whole fruit, or just a peel, be sure to cut off both ends of the banana. Place the peel or the entire banana into a pot with a few cups of water. Boil for about 10 minutes.
.
Pour the tea through a strainer or colander and allow it to cool before drinking. You may prefer to add a little more flavor (and medicinal benefit) with #cinnamon or a bit of #honey. Both of these offer antifungal and antibacterial properties and help #reduceinflammation too.

If you follow my work, you know that I talk often about how what you put ON your skin gets absorbed into your body, and it bioaccumulates in your FAT CELLS 😱 This means it builds up in our bodies and has a cumulative effect. So when we're talking about makeup, something we put on our bodies every.single.day, it's REALLY important to be aware of what we're exposing ourselves to. . Some common harmful chemicals you'll find in your makeup are things like fragrance, phthalates, petroleum byproducts, parabens, and SLS. . Let's talk about some of the other things you might find in your cosmetics: 👎 Artificial colors : often made from coal tars, artificial colors often contain heavy metals (including lead), and can be associated with thyroid tumors, allergic reactions, and kidney tumors. 👎 Talc: it's a mineral substance used to absorb moisture and soften products. Talc use is linked to endometrial and ovarian cancer. It can cause severe respiratory distress because it damages the epithelial lining of the lungs. 👎Bismuth: its a naturally occurring heavy metal that actually resembles arsenic (chemically) and is OFTEN used in "safe" mineral makeup! As far as we know, this one is not linked to cancer, however it can be extremely irritating to the skin and do some major pore-clogging. . YL's Savvy Minerals makeup is vegan and cruelty free! It's made with all minerals and some have our own pure essential oils <3 . Personally, I have to tell you that since I switched to Savvy and using young living's frankinscense on my skin, my skin has never been clearer and more glowing. Ever. column31: It’s true. Most people don’t report vaccine adverse events because they don’t know WHAT is an adverse event. People are told a fussy, crying baby after shots is normal. That redness and swelling, even the high-pitched crying is normal. They’ll say give some Tylenol. And that these are signs the vaccines are working. Parents are told that their babies just suddenly became allergic to their mother’s breastmilk. Or maybe some new foods in YOUR diet. They’ll say some babies just get eczema, hives, or sleep a lot after shots. That diarrhea is only worrisome if it has blood in it. Arching, silent reflux, it’s all just normal baby stuff. Failure to thrive, lack of weight gain, lack of growth, loss of cooing or words. Joint pain, muscle pain, suddenly not wanting to bear weight. Purple crying, apnea, BRUE, seizures, SIDS. Ear infections, pneumonia, bronchitis. RSV after a Dtap? Heard that one too many times. Do they help you? When you call? What do they tell you to do?? In 2011, HHS funded a research team that "to improve the quality of vaccination programs by improving the quality of physician adverse vaccine event detection and reporting to the national Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System (VAERS).” However, what they found was: "Adverse events from drugs and vaccines are common, but underreported. Although 25% of ambulatory patients experience an adverse drug event, less than 0.3% of all adverse drug events and 1-13% of serious events are reported to the Food and Drug Administration (FDA). Likewise, fewer than 1% of vaccine adverse events are reported. Low reporting rates preclude or slow the identification of “problem” drugs and vaccines that endanger public health." https://digital.ahrq.gov/sites/default/files/docs/publication/r18hs017045-lazarus-final-report-2011.pdf ✖️TO REPORT A VACCINE REACTION: VAERS.HHS.GOV✖️

Mercuric chloride went by the name Calomel (not shown) and was a very popular medicine to treat a range of illnesses mumps, typhoid fever, and others—especially those that impact the gastrointestinal tract, such as constipation, dysentery, and vomiting. 2. The 'silent highway'-man. A strong visual response to the problems caused by the very hot summer of 1858. This resulted in a terrible smell from the Thames caused by the high level of sewage and pollution. The cartoon shows death silently rowing a boat on the polluted river with dead animals floating by. 3. A woman emptying her chamber pot, aka. her personal waste pot. Just out the window! I think many people have a certain image of human health throughout history, namely that: for thousands of years humans had ill-health and short life spans, that only improved with the advent of modern medicine, after which they experienced better and improving health, and longer life spans. In this view, modern medicine is credited as the humble hero. However, humans have been living into their 70s and 80s for thousands of years. And in light of medical error being the third leading cause of death nationwide, and that 70,000 Americans die annually from drug overdose, 63% of them doctor-prescribed, and the other two leading causes: cancer and heart disease are largely environmentally caused–I’m going to have to disagree with you. But it’s interesting to note two things: human civilization created the conditions for disease, and doctors were mistrusted–even back then. Infectious diseases did not become a “plague” to humans until humans settled down into large civilizations and began farming. The intersection of larger civilizations, as opposed to smaller hunter-gatherer nomadic groups, the new habit of eating single crops, as opposed to a variety of foraged nutrient-dense foods, and the piling up of human waste and refuse, created the perfect storm for diseases to breed and take hold. Back when doctors were pushing concoctions of mercurous chloride and opium, bloodletting and purging, and practicing what was called “heroic medicine” that always ended in a patient dying anyways, Joseph Addison wrote in The Spectator in 1711: “If we look into the profession of the physic, we shall find the most formidable body of men. The sight of them is enough to make a man serious, for we may lay it down as a maxim, that when a nation abounds in physicians it grows thin of people.” READ MORE: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/injecting-poisons-a-history-of-the-syringe/

column31: If you're just joining us, we're working on a series on medical practice and freedom in the US. We've covered the start of the country through the early 1900s and the Flexner Report, and now we're going to look at early 1900s medical freedom.... While the 'regulars' were busy petitioning the government to fund their allopathic ways, and create laws to force others out of practice, not everyone agreed with what was going on. Russell Trall, MD, was one of them. He was part of the 'hygienics' movement (later known as naturopaths) who believed in drugless healing -- and, in empowering individuals to mostly take care of themselves. He was a prolific writer, creating several books with symptoms and remedies for the average person to use to help themselves. Trall also opposed the use of surgery and vaccines (and this was in the mid-1800s!). Benjamin O Flowers was another. He was the founder of the National League of Medical Freedom, an early group dedicated to preserving medical freedom! He opposed a new law that would create a federal department of health, worried that if the federal government had any power to direct health, that people would lose the freedom to choose their own health modalities and treatments entirely.... Sadly, the opposition was not strong enough to overcome the effects of the Flexner report, and the massive amounts of cash from Carnegie and Rockefeller (two non-medical billionaires who had financial incentives to see "science-based" medicine flourish) and allopathic medicine began to creep in, more and more....

column31: If you’ve recently had a blood test, you might assume it would show a magnesium deficiency. But only 1 percent of magnesium in your body is distributed in your blood, making a simple sample of magnesium from a serum magnesium blood test not very useful. Most magnesium is stored in your bones and organs, where it is used for many biological functions. Yet, it’s quite possible to be deficient and not know it, which is why magnesium deficiency has been dubbed the “invisible deficiency."
column35: 22 Problems Caused by Magnesium Deficiency and The Subtle Warning Signs
column36: Magnesium is a mineral used by every organ in your body, especially your heart, muscles, and kidneys.1 If you suffer from unexplained fatigue or weakness, abnormal heart rhythms or even muscle spasms and eye twitches, low levels of magnesium could be to blame.

column31: Homeschooling is NOT "school at home." It does not require set hours. It does not require desks or a formal set up. It does not require several hours for young kids. It does not require curriculum. The state does not set your standards or tell you what to do. Homeschooling means YOU choose what is important to you and what works. Cooking, cleaning, playing, fun reading, art projects -- all count as learning. column31: If you're just joining us, we're working on a series on medical practice and freedom in the US. We've covered the start of the country through the 1800s, and now we're going to look at a BIG event that took place in 1910.... The Carnegie Foundation was not the only foundation that was investing in this new, "science-based" medicine. John D Rockefeller, and his foundation, the Rockefeller Foundation was, too. If you think that the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation has had a big impact on 21st century medicine, the Rockefeller Foundation had just as big an impact on 20th century medicine...maybe even more. Rockefeller, like Carnegie and Gates, had absolutely no medical training or expertise. He was a billionaire who created a "philanthrophic" organization that he ran like a business, trying to push this new medicine on the entire world. In America, the Carnegie Foundation commissioned what is commonly referred to as the "Flexner Report." Abraham Flexner, a professor (also with zero medical background) traveled around the country for 18 months, visiting all of the medical schools, for a few hours each. He then graded them all, and issued a 200+ page report, with scathing language towards all of the 'alternative' schools (essentially, for not having modern labs or following allopathic ideas). He convinced Congress that there should be a set of "standards" by which ALL doctors should practice...basically, allopathic standards! Rockefeller, an oil magnate, knew that he and others could make huge amounts of money by backing this new "science based" medicine, because they could make and patent synthetic drugs to kill the newly-discovered bacteria (and they could use his oil to create some of those drugs...WIN for him). Over the next few years, nearly all of the non-allopathic medical schools would close. The allopathic doctors had wanted to be seen as experts, a privileged class of men, and they got their wish because of the Flexner report. They believed that medicine was only for the highly educated, and that people should have to consult with experts to get information -- and do as they were told. Of course, not everyone thought that way! The next post will show what else was going on during this time....

column31: “Although India’s last case of polio was reported in 2011, a surveillance system continues to annually investigate some 50,000 cases of acute flaccid paralysis (AFP) — defined as a sudden onset of paralysis or weakness in any part of the body of a child under 15 years of age. While no case of AFP has tested positive for polio since 2012, the rate of non-polio paralysis has continued to be unusually high, especially in the northern states of Bihar and Uttar Pradesh which together have a population of 300 million people. “In the absence of wild polio transmission, it was expected that cases of paralysis would reduce to an acceptable rate of around two per 100,000, but this has not materialised,” Puliyel tells SciDev.Net. The study found the paralysis rate to be as high as 30 per 100,000 people in Bihar and Uttar Pradesh. The study showed that the number of pulse polio rounds (immunisation campaigns) conducted in a state had a "high correlation" with the non-polio paralysis rate. "We found that the … rates in Bihar and Uttar Pradesh were higher in those years when the pulse polio rounds conducted were more frequent," says Puliyel. The findings suggest that oral polio vaccinations were responsible for inducing paralysis. Madhavi Yennapu, principal scientist at the National Institute of Science, Technology and Development Studies in New Delhi, cautions that the study needs to be validated with serological data. “The real effects of OPV on the immune system of individuals as well as on herd immunity need to be studied, as well as potentially adverse changes to the microbiome,” she says. The authors suggest that "repeated doses of the live virus vaccine delivered to the intestine may colonise the gut and alter the viral microbiome of the intestine". A microbiome is formed of an ecological community of friendly or pathogenic microorganisms that share body spaces. Of these, the gut microbiome is known to change quickly over the first two to three years of life and continues to change according to factors such as diet, environment and treatment with antibiotics or oral vaccines. "While the mechanism involved is speculative, our findings support the hypothesis that the frequency of pulse polio administration is directly or indirectly related to the incidence of non-polio AFP," the authors write. "Now that India has been polio-free for over six years, we may be able to reduce non-polio AFP by further reducing pulse polio rounds." https://www.scidev.net/global/disease/news/oral-polio-drops-linked-to-paralysis-in-india-1x.html

column31: Check the media, and there are always dark, vague warnings about the "dangers" of alternative medicine. We decided to dive in and see what evidence there actually was.... Some studies show as many as 70% of Americans are using at least one prescription drug at any given time. Many of them end up hospitalized due to adverse reactions, and several die. The estimations here are based on people using drugs each year vs. the known number of adverse reactions and deaths. Now, the mainstream likes to make several arguments about the true "dangers" of alternative medicine, all of which read like conspiracy theories (because they are). First they start out with, not that many people use it, so the risks to those who do are probably greater -- but that's not true. About a third of all people in the US use at least one herbal remedy each year. Then they mutter about how supplements are "unregulated" and "untracked" and we have no idea how many people MIGHT be having adverse reactions. But they can't pull out more than a small handful of cases studies -- typically 8 - 10 per year. (Fewer than 1 in a million!) There's not exactly a huge upswell of users complaining about how terrible herbs are and demanding they be pulled off the market...unlike some pharmaceutical products we can think of. It's true that the majority of adverse reactions that have been documented from supplements occurred either as allergic reactions, improper use, improperly made supplements, or were never proven to be tied to the supplement at all (just "associated with"). Almost never do properly-made, properly-used supplements cause adverse effects, outside of allergies. Finally, they get upset because herbal supplements are "preventing people from using real medicine" (by which they mean allopathy). First of all, looking at these numbers, that seems like it's a GOOD thing in some cases.... It also doesn't take into consideration the number of people who are choosing herbal remedies because allopathy already failed to work for them. Why does the mainstream give allopathy and all its damages a free pass, while darkly condemning herbal remedies without any evidence to do so? Their dire, anti-science rantings sound like the "tin foil hat" nonsense they accuse *us* of! Smart people are capable of cutting through the lies and looking at the data for themselves. And smart people will clearly see the truth here, and choose the safest option whenever possible -- natural.

column36:
Whatever supplement you choose, be sure to #avoid any containing #magnesium stearate, a common but potentially #hazardous additive.

-Magnesium glycinate is a chelated form of magnesium that tends to provide the highest levels of absorption and bioavailability and is typically considered ideal for those who are trying to correct a deficiency.
-Magnesium chloride / Magnesium lactate contain only 12 percent magnesium but has better absorption than others, such as magnesium oxide, which contains five times more magnesium.
-Magnesium carbonate, which has antacid properties, contains 45 percent magnesium.
-Magnesium citrate is magnesium with citric acid, which has laxative properties.
-Magnesium oxide is a non-chelated type of magnesium, bound to an organic acid or a fatty acid. Contains 60 percent magnesium, and has stool softening properties.
-Magnesium sulfate / Magnesium hydroxide (milk of magnesia) are typically used as laxatives. Be aware that it’s easy to overdose on these, so ONLY take as directed.
-Magnesium taurate contains a combination of magnesium and taurine, an amino acid. Together, they tend to provide a calming effect on your body and mind.
-Magnesium threonate is a newer, emerging type of magnesium supplement that appears promising, primarily due to its superior ability to penetrate the mitochondrial membrane, and maybe the best magnesium supplement on the market.

column31: Aware friends, today, let's talk the Immune System and Molds. Many clients will scan for molds and/or have symptoms of mold toxitity and perhaps not even know the connection. Having these assessed and cleared by a skilled root cause practitioner will be important for short and long terms healing. Our immune systems protect us from dangerous pathogens, like bacteria, including Lyme’s Borrelia burgdorferi, parasites, viruses, and fungi (including mold). It shields us from the harmful substances we encounter, including environmental toxins, heavy metals, biotoxins, and more. White blood cells, called lymphocytes, carry out adaptive immune responses. There are two broad classes of these responses: cell-mediated immune responses and antibody responses. They are carried out by different types of lymphocytes, called T cells and B cells, respectively. In the cell-mediated immune response, activated T cells take direct action against foreign antigens. T cells might kill an infected or toxic host cell. Or, the T cell might produce a signal molecule that activates macrophages which engulf and destroy invaders, toxins, and cellular debris. Activated B cells secrete antibodies–proteins called immunoglobulins. The antibodies circulate in the system, where they bind specifically to the foreign antigens, inactivating the mold biotoxins. As a result, the biotoxins can no longer bind to receptors on host cells. Mycotoxin exposure comes from ingestion, dermal transmission, and inhalation. Mold toxins are extremely potent and often affect nearly every organ system in the body. Some of the symptoms associated with Chronic Inflammatory Response Syndrome (CIRS) include: +Brain fog, memory issues, cognitive and focus difficulties +Mood swings +Digestive problems +Fatigue; weakness +Frequent urination; excessive thirst; dehydration +Weight gain +Muscle and joint pain +Blurry vision; light sensitivity +Postnasal drip; sore throat +Numbness; tingling +Tinnitus +Static shocks +Dizziness +Metallic taste in the mouth +Low-grade fever +Shortness of breath +Headache Key elements of the immune system which I bioscan assess for clients include: 📈 +Spleen Your spleen helps your body fight infection. Just as it quality checks red blood cells, your spleen can identify unwelcome pathogens in your blood. In conjunction with the lymph nodes, it creates an organized force of defender cells called lymphocytes. Lymphocytes are specific white blood cells that produce antibodies. +Lymph Nodes These are nodes, vessels, and tissues located throughout the body, including in the neck, armpits, abdomen, and groin. The lymph nodes help break down harmful germs. Also, they filter toxins for removal from the body in lymph fluid. White blood cells contained in the lymph nodes help fight infection. +Bone Marrow Bone marrow is the spongy tissue located inside some of the bones in the body, such as the hip and thigh bones. Bone marrow makes 200 billion new red blood cells every day.3 It also produces white blood cells and platelets. If the bone marrow isn’t functioning well and produces abnormal white blood cells, those cells may be unable to fight infection. +White Blood Cells The bone marrow produces white blood cells, or leukocytes. These are crucial for a healthy immune system. They fight and protect against infections. They are stored in the spleen, the bone marrow, and the lymph nodes. White blood cells can circulate throughout the body. They collect in areas where there is an infection. +Mycotoxins can significantly impair the antibody production of the adaptive immune system. column31: If you're just joining us, we're working on a series on medical practice and freedom in the US. We've covered the start of the country through most of the 1800s; now we're going to cover what happened in the mid/late 1800s and early 1900s. In 1848, the American Medical Association was founded. This gave 'regular' physicians power than alternatives didn't have. (Competing, natural-minded organizations were formed, but disbanded years later; the various drugless modalities couldn't agree on a path and never gained the political power that the 'regulars' had.) The AMA quickly tried to set the standards for how medicine should be practiced -- including that Black people and women shouldn't be permitted to practice! They simply assumed that they were right and should be in charge. But the AMA didn't make that much headway...until the very last part of the 1800s and early 1900s. At this point, more modern scientific methods were first discovered...doctors began to believe in germ theory, and use lab tests. They were convinced that these were the foundation of the medicine of the future (a future where all disease was caused by specific organism, and all we had to do was use drugs to kill them in order to be healthy). Since the other modalities weren't using these newly-discovered 'scientific' methods very much, it was easy for the 'regular' physicians to convince the government and the public that they were simply right, and other modalities should go away. They got a big boost towards this end from the Carnegie Foundation in the late 1800s. The Foundation was created by Andrew Carnegie, steel magnate. (He's been referred to as the "Bill Gates of his day" and like Gates, had no medical training whatsoever.) But it wasn't until 1910 that the BIG changes happened....

A three-day-old baby died in a government hospital in Tripura's Agartala on Wednesday, August 12, allegedly after a nurse inserted a nasal swab to take samples for its COVID-19 test. 

The incident took place in the city's biggest COVID-19 treatment facility -- GB Pant government hospital. 

According to the baby's family, the nurse took samples of the infant after the mother tested positive for the infection. Soon after the cotton swabs were inserted, the infant started bleeding from the nose. It died on the same day. "They must not have taken the sample with the delicacy it required to handle a three-day-old infant and may have damaged a vein inside because the child started bleeding which didn't stop," NDTV quoted a family member as saying.

column31: We often hear people say "You have to cook elderberries or they're toxic! They can cause cyanide poisoning!" Well, we finally decided to look it up and see what the evidence for that claim was.... In the 1980s, someone made elderberry juice -- from crushing the berries AND stems and leaves.... 10 people drank this juice, one person had 5 glasses. All of those people had nausea and vomiting within an hour of drinking the juice. One was hospitalized, everyone recovered without incident in a day or two. Cyanide levels in the body were NORMAL. The species of the plant was sambucus mexicana (today we mostly use sambucus nigra). So. Improperly made juice that included the known-to-be-toxic stems and leaves. Brief illness with no long-term damage or death. Wrong species of elderberry plant. There are NO other official reports of toxicity stemming from elderberry consumption. A few people tell anecdotes online about how they were already sick, had raw elderberry (and other stuff) and then got sicker for a few hours. There's no solid evidence that elderberry is toxic. In fact, some sources say the ripe berries don't contain the glucoside that is metabolized to a cyanide-like chemical in the body. Others say this chemical is an inert form. Basically? Don't eat the roots, stems, leaves, or unripe berries. Don't worry about elderberry syrups and tinctures not being "heated enough." They are not poisonous. It's important to ask more questions, always...and not just pass on information because "everyone knows..." Everyone might be wrong. Sources: https://www.acs.org/content/acs/en/molecule-of-the-week/archive/s/sambunigrin.html https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/00000311.htm https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/27734518:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27734518/

column31: If you're just joining us, we're working on a series on medical practice and freedom in the US. We've covered the start of the country; here's what happened in the 1800s! Allopathic practice -- a term that had not yet been coined; physicians called themselves "regulars" and all other modalities "irregular" -- was just emerging. It was extremely barbaric, with doctors using bloodletting, leeches, and heavy metals to try to 'cure' patients. Even so, they were as arrogant as they are today, assuming that they should be the dominant form of medicine. The regular physicians tried to force the government to create licensing laws that would allow them to practice officially, but would bar practitioners of newly-created homeopathy, eclecticism, naturopathy, chiropractic, and other drugless modalities. Many people disagreed (including the drugless practitioners!) and argued that medical freedom was important -- everyone had a right to choose what health modality worked for them. Licensing laws actually got repealed, for awhile. Things were going okay, with each modality having plenty of fans, until the late 1800s.... See our next post to learn what happened next!

column31: People keep saying this -- that since doctors and nurses wear masks, that must mean everyone else can, too. Setting aside the fact that a reasonably healthy medical professional is NOT like someone who might be in less-than-optimal health (or a growing, developing child), these things are not comparable for several reasons.⁠ ⁠ *Doctors do not wear CLOTH masks that let viral particles through but trap larger bacteria -- right against their face.⁠ *Doctors do not wear masks for 8+ hours with no breaks.⁠ *Doctors do not wear the SAME mask for days on end (they are supposed to get a new mask every 3 - 4 hours).⁠ *Doctors do not wear masks from one contaminated environment into another.⁠ *Doctors do not put on or remove masks with unwashed hands.⁠ *Doctors do not eat or drink in their masks.⁠ ⁠ All of these behaviors increase the risks and decrease the benefits of mask wearing. We have to stop making brazen comparisons without considering how different the situations really are!

column35: Physicians for Informed Consent
column36:
Breaking News, Newport Beach, CA:  Physicians for Informed Consent Publishes New Educational Document on Risk of Aluminum in Vaccines 

Physicians for Informed Consent (PIC), an educational nonprofit organization focused on science and statistics, has just released its Aluminum Vaccine Risk Statement (VRS) entitled “Aluminum in Vaccines: What Parents Need to Know.” The educational document answers important questions about the risks of aluminum-containing vaccines administered to newborns, infants and children.

“The COVID-19 pandemic has shown us that the public is very interested in weighing the risks of infectious diseases versus the risks of vaccines,” said Dr. Shira Miller, PIC founder and president. “Parents and the public must become knowledgeable about aluminum in vaccines because even though it is used as an adjuvant in many vaccines, it is a neurotoxin—and overexposure may lead to significant harm, including problems in motor, sensory, and cognitive function.” Currently, up to 22 doses of aluminum-containing vaccines are recommended to children, with 11 doses recommended from birth to 6 months of age.

The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) and the Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry (ATSDR), agencies of the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (HHS), have raised concerns about the negative effects of aluminum exposure in humans. In scientific studies, small amounts of aluminum that remain in the body have been observed to interfere with a variety of cellular and metabolic processes in the nervous system and in tissues of other parts of the body. Some of the most damaging effects of aluminum range from motor skill impairment to encephalopathy (altered mental state, personality changes, difficulty thinking, loss of memory, seizures, coma, and more). 

The FDA states that if some vaccines did not include aluminum (i.e., aluminum hydroxide and aluminum phosphate) as an adjuvant, the immune response they trigger may be diminished. Therefore, aluminum is included in many vaccines on the childhood schedule, including the following: hepatitis B (HepB), Haemophilus influenzae type b (PedvaxHIB), pneumococcal (PCV), hepatitis A (HepA), human papillomavirus (HPV), meningococcal B (MenB), and diphtheria, tetanus, and pertussis (DTaP and Tdap). 

“Vaccines are administered preventively to healthy people, not people with acute or chronic infections, so it’s crucially important to know the safety data upon which one’s recommendations are based,” said Dr. Miller. “PIC developed the Aluminum VRS to help families and their physicians advance their understanding of the risks of aluminum adjuvants, so they may engage in informed decision-making.” 

Parents and caregivers are encouraged to discuss the Aluminum VRS educational documents with their children’s doctor. To read the Aluminum VRS or to download it, please visit http://physiciansforinformedconsent.org/aluminum.:=:https://physiciansforinformedconsent.org/aluminum/

column36:
Over the weekend, Baby Eleanor suffered a tragic accident that resulted in her being declared brain dead. With only two days in the hospital, the family was told they could no longer keep their 22 month old daughter on life support. Against their wishes, Arnold Palmer Hospital in Orlando, Florida, told the family they had until 3pm EST today before life support would be pulled.⠀
⠀
Together, our community called the hospital and reached out to lawyers and medical personnel, doing everything we could to extend Baby Eleanor’s time on life support. Within an hour, Arnold Palmer hospital then notified the family they had another 24-48 hours.⠀
⠀
To our disappointment, just hours later, the family was then notified they did not have the 24-48 hours as promised and would instead only have until 8am EST.⠀
⠀
The Polyakov family is accepting donations to help support legal fees they may have or medical bills. Please consider donating to them.⠀
⠀
As a mother, I would stop the world any which way I could to save the life of my child and give our family more time to make choices that are informed and to ensure I know without a doubt, that we are making the right decision. 

Please say a little prayer and ask for a miracle for this baby girl.

column31: Christopher Eugene Bunch 12/5/03-8/14/18 💔🙏 Two years ago today, Christopher Eugene Bunch died from complications of the Gardasil vaccine. He developed the severe vaccine injury known as ADEM, or Acute Disseminated Encephalomyelitis, in the weeks following the administration of the aluminum-loaded Gardasil vaccine against human papillomavirus (HPV). ADEM is an autoimmune disorder in which the body's immune system mistakenly attacks its own brain tissue, triggered by an environmental stimulus in genetically susceptible individuals. ADEM has occurred after Gardasil, but can occur after any vaccine, like the DTP vaccine, the influenza vaccine, and the Hep B vaccine. ADEM typically begins with inflammation that develops 7-14 days after an infection or vaccine, which simulates infection in the body, and triggers a similar immune response. Because vaccines contain aluminum adjuvants, the immune response may be too strong for some people. It is currently not known why some people develop ADEM, and others do not. According to VAERS, the time interval from vaccination to ADEM onset was 2-30 days in 61% of the cases. Please read and share his story and keep his family in your prayers and hearts: https://christopherbunch.org/ . https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/remembering-christopher-bunch-a-life-taken-by-gardasil/:=:https://circleofmamas.com/vaccine-injury-stories/remembering-christopher-bunch-a-life-taken-by-gardasil/ #christopherbunch #rememberchristopher #neverforgetchris #gonetoosoon #gardasil #hpvvaccine

column36:
Have you heard of Malunggay?
.
#Malunggay can help strengthen the body to fight off #disease before it ever starts, thanks to the #immuneboosting nutrients it possesses. An excellent source of #vitamin A, vitamins B and C, iron and other #minerals, plus amino acids methionine and cystine, this leafy green is commonly used in #salads or as a side dish in the same way spinach is used. But lately, in light of all the #health news surrounding the benefits of malunggay, cooks have been getting adventurous with it. These days you’ll find it in pasta dishes, soups, and even bread. The seeds themselves can be ground up and used as a seasoning, and not to be outdone, the roots and flowers can be part of the action too. The roots are spicy, similar to #horseradish, and make a great seasoning base for dishes of all kinds that could use a little extra kick. The flowers make a lovely (and visually interesting) addition to salads.

column31: Friends, question for you, have you heard this story before? Read to the end. I’d love for you to weigh in. *A Tale of ✌Two Theories: So there was once this guy name Louis Pasteur. Does his name sound familiar? He was the guy that discovered "pasteurizing" milk products. He was also the man behind the Germ Theory. This is the idea that germs are what make us sick! So in order to stay healthy, we need to kill off all of the germs! Then there's this other guy. His name was Antoine BeChampe. He was actually a contemporary of Pasteur's, and he was the guy behind the Terrain Theory. While BeChampe was researching, he observed that germs were opportunist in nature (remember, Pasteur believed that viruses and bacteria... germs.. were what killed people). They were EVERYWHERE and even existed inside of us and on us in a symbiotic relationship. BeChampe noticed in his research that it was only when the tissue of the host became damaged or compromised that these germs began to manifest as a prevailing symptom (not cause of) disease. To prevent illness, Bechampe advocated not the killing of germs but the cultivation of health through diet, hygiene, and healthy lifestyle practices. The idea here is that if a person has a strong immune system and good tissue quality (or "terrain" as Bechampe called it), the germs will not manifest in the person. It's only when their health starts to decline that they become victim to infections. The practice of Western or allopathic medicine (although it has its place) is based on Pasteur's germ phobia which gives rise to the use of antibiotics, biologics (which contain antibiotics), and other anti-microbial agents. Let's use the example of a fish. Imagine a fish in a fish bowl. As the bowl gets dirty and fills up with junk, what do you do? Do you dump a bunch of chemicals in the fish bowl and expect the fish to be "healthy"? Or do you clean out the tank and give it fresh water? column31: I’ve always suspected this. When my kids were little I really restricted their screen time. I allowed them 30 minutes a week. Yup, that was ONE show per week! 🙃 I told them “It’s better to LIVE life than just to *watch* it.” Why sit passively, absorbing some program (& notice the word w/ all of its implications) when you can be playing, jumping, exploring, or dancing? 💫 So, yeah, they had a little FOMO but mostly they had a LOT of fun! 😀 And now they thank me that they didn’t have the television (tell-a-vision) educating them about how to live or be. Today my children are critical thinkers. And I can’t help but credit, in part, the lack of tv-watching for their relational, emotional & intellectual maturity. (The other part is good genetics of course! 😉) There are so many reasons I recommend turning off the TV, whether you’re a kid or adult! Television: 1️⃣ fosters passivity & receptivity 2️⃣ wastes time 3️⃣ entertains (holds captive) 4️⃣ emits blue light that interferes w/ hormone function Instead I recommend: ☀️ blue skies & sunshine ☀️ connecting IRL ☀️ thinking ☀️ living ☺️ Am I too hard on TV? Or do you see it as the health hazard/life hazard that I do? ☀️ ☀️ ☀️ Cuando mis niños eran chiquitos yo les limitaba la televisión. Solo les permitía ver media hora a la semana de tele. Un programa, nada más. Sí se quejaban de vez en cuando pero valió la pena porque vivieron su niñez en vez de estar ante una pantalla viendo la vida de otros. Y eso para qué? Se me hizo mucho mejor que jugaran, exploraran, bailaran, y cantaran. Y hoy me agradecen el hecho de que les haya prohibido más tele. Mis hijos hoy día son inteligentes e independientes, gracias, yo creo, al hecho de que pasaron más tiempo pensando y experimentando la vida que otra cosa. Y yo todavía recomiendo para niños de todas edades 😁que se limiten las horas ante la tele. Porque la televisión: 1️⃣ presenta muchas boberías 2️⃣ nos hace perder tiempo 3️⃣ entretiene (y no suelta) 4️⃣ emite luz azul que interfiere con nuestro equilibrio hormonal Mi prescripción holística: ☀️ sol y naturaleza ☀️ conexiones en la vida real ☀️ pensar ☀️ vivir ☺️ Qué opinas tú? Es así de dañino la tele? O exagero?

column31: It should be *extremely* concerning to everyone that, when facing a global pandemic (however it got here and however serious it may or may not be) that the ONLY solution that officials have to offer is a vaccine. A vaccine that does not exist. A vaccine that may never exist. A vaccine that may have significant side effects. A vaccine the government has already committed $2 billion to purchase. A vaccine they are already talking about forcing on everyone. We HAVE to be able and willing to think outside the box to solve problems and create health. If this pandemic had been more deadly than it is, pinning hopes on an undeveloped vaccine that was months or years away would have led to millions of unnecessary deaths. And when it first started, and they were already talking about the necessity of a vaccine, they didn't know it wasn't. Why do we let officials do this? Why don't we hold them accountable? We have to deal with *reality* and have a variety of potential solutions. Not this fantasy world in which vaccines solve all problems. When can we talk about other, rational, SAFE solutions to keep people healthy? Will our society ever be ready for that conversation?

column35: This is a re-share of a post
column36:
At 10:36 pm exactly a year ago I tried to wake Remy up for one of the final times. He fell unconscious at 2:35 pm, just 15 minutes after his CDC recommended schedule, and I was unsuccessful in waking him all day. I tried at 10:36 and tried to feed him. He wouldn’t wake up, he just stirred. I figured I’d change his diaper and get him to eat some. His diaper was almost dry. 8 hours after he last got a diaper change. He still didn’t want to eat. I swaddled him back up and laid him back down thinking he’d feel better in the morning. Little did I know he was dying in front of my eyes and I didn’t even realize it. Looking back I see so many red flags that make me angry I didn’t do more. But even if I had taken him to the hospital would it have saved him? The damage had already been done and I would have been assured “it’s normal” 
SWELLING OF THE BRAIN AFTER VACCINES IS NOT NORMAL!!!!!!!!!! DEATH AFTER VACCINES IS NOT NORMAL!!!!!!!!!! 
#RememberRemy

Infants–6 months: 30 milligrams

1–3 years: 80 milligrams
4–8 years: 130 milligrams
9–13 years: 240 milligrams
14–18 years: 410 milligrams for men; 360 milligrams for women

Adults 31 years and older: 420 milligrams for men; 320 milligrams for women
#Pregnant women: 350–360 milligrams
Women who are #breastfeeding: 310–320 milligrams

column31: On paper, the Vaccine Injury Compensation Program seems like it would compensate and take care of victims of vaccine injury. But the reality is that most injuries don’t qualify for compensation, and many legitimate petitions are denied. The VICP is not there to protect families of vaccine injury. It’s there to protect vaccine manufacturers and those physicians and pharmacists who inject them. Right now, HHS is trying to remove two vaccine injuries from the already extremely limited Vaccine Injury Table: Vasavagal syncope and SIRVA (shoulder injury related to vaccine administration). They would be removing them because they are denying that they are caused by the vaccine contents, alleging improper administration. This would not result in liability for vaccine makers, but it would for the person who injects them. While we want the 1986 Act repealed, removing injuries will not protect the people. The science is actually demonstrating these injuries are vaccine related (vaccines are injections, and there are no alternatives to injecting), and these conditions are increased in vaccinated people. Petitioners may be caught in a loop between two entities where both deny responsibility, and end up with absolutely nothing. Leave a public comment: https://www.regulations.gov/document?D=HRSA-2020-0002-0001 Proposed rule making: https://www.hrsa.gov/sites/default/files/hrsa/vaccine-compensation/federal-register-nprm-vaccine-injury-table.pdf The COVID-19 vaccine may eventually be placed on the recommended schedule, and these two injuries would be removed prior to the approval of the new vaccine.

column36:
Health Benefits Of #Magnesium
1. Helps Increase #Energy
Magnesium creates “energy” in the body by activating adenosine triphosphate, or ATP. Without enough magnesium, you can suffer from fatigue more easily. One study found that when magnesium-deficient women exercised, their bodies required more oxygen and had a higher heart rate than women whose levels were higher.
.
2. Calms #Nerves and #Anxiety
Magnesium is needed for healthy GABA function, which produces “feel-good hormones” such as serotonin. Magnesium also regulates hormones that are responsible for promoting relaxation. A 2012 study looked at magnesium-deficient mice, and found that they displayed anxiety-related behaviors when compared to mice who were given supplements.
.
3. Treats #Insomnia and Helps You Fall Asleep
Magnesium may help quiet a racing mind, making it easier to get a good night’s sleep. Our circadian rhythms change, in particular as we age, thanks to our decreased nutrient consumption and a lower #nutrient absorption. This can put us at risk for insomnia.
.
In an experiment where 46 patients were given #magnesiumsupplements or a placebo, the group taking magnesium supplements experienced a significant increase in sleep time, an easier time falling asleep, higher concentrations of melatonin (the hormone responsible for inducing sleepiness) and lower levels of cortisol, which are associated with stress.
For more info: https://bit.ly/39TAR3J:=:https://www.mykoreessentials.com/shop/magnesium-oil.html?utm_source=Facebook&utm_medium=Social&utm_campaign=OGmag

column31: Because their fear mongering tactics didn't work, the Federal Government and Yale are now working on different techniques to "persuade" us into taking the Covid-19 Vaccine. The options they are studying include shame and anger techniques. A few of these techniques are: Baseline message - These participants will be assigned a message about the the effectiveness and safety of vaccines. Personal freedom - Limiting people's personal freedom and by working together to get enough people vaccinated society can preserve its personal freedom. Self-interest message - COVID-19 presents a real danger to one's health, even if one is young and healthy. Getting vaccinated against COVID-19 is the best way to prevent oneself from getting sick. Community interest message - The dangers of COVID-19 to the health of loved ones. The more people who get vaccinated against COVID-19, the lower the risk that one's loved ones will get sick. Economic benefit message - How COVID-19 is wreaking havoc on the economy and the only way to strengthen the economy is to work together to get enough people vaccinated. Guilt message - The best way to protect them is by getting vaccinated and society must work together to get enough people vaccinated. Then it asks the participant to imagine the guilt they will feel if they don't get vaccinated and spread the disease. Embarrassment message - Asks the participant to imagine the embarrassment they will feel if they don't get vaccinated and spread the disease. Anger message - Asks the participant to imagine the anger they will feel if they don't get vaccinated and spread the disease. Trust in science message - Getting vaccinated against COVID-19 is the most effective way of protecting one's community. Vaccination is backed by science. If one doesn't get vaccinated that means that one doesn't understand how infections are spread or who ignores science. Not bravery message - Describes how firefighters, doctors, and front line medical workers are brave. Those who choose not to get vaccinated against COVID-19 are not brave. Why does our government have to manipulate us? Shouldn't they be more worried about making sure the vaccine is properly tested, and also looking at already-existing methods of keeping people healthy? This is way over the line. column31: We want to be clear that we do NOT support mandates of any kind. But... if its truly about health, why not breastfeeding?! Worldwide, exclusive breastfeeding for 6 months could save an estimated 800,000 lives and $300 billion in health care costs every YEAR. Children who are breastfeed perform better in intelligence tests, are less likely to be overweight or obese, and less prone to diabetes later in life. Mothers who breastfeed also reduce their risk of developing breast and ovarian cancers. At current breastfeeding rates, an estimated 20,000 deaths from breast cancer are prevented and an additional 20,000 could be saved if rates improved. Boosting breastfeeding rates for infants below 6 months of age to 90% would cut treatment costs of common childhood illnesses, and save healthcare systems at least US$ 2.45 billion in the United States, US$ 29.5 million in the United Kingdom, US$ 223.6 million in China, and US$ 6.0 million in Brazil. Although a mother's milk is valuable for all babies, premature babies may have the most to gain from breastfeeding. Preemie deaths are most often caused by: -Sudden infant death syndrome (SIDS). -Lower respiratory infections such as pneumonia. -Necrotizing enterocolitis, in which the lining of the intestinal wall dies. Studies show breastfeeding can reduce these risks, as well as seven other illnesses that have been linked to deaths among premature babies. Could you imagine the HUGE difference that more breastfeeding would make in overall human health? Yet, breastfeeding rates haven't significantly changed in 20 years, because they are more interested in mandating dangerous health products than supporting good health behaviors. https://www.who.int/maternal_child_adolescent/news_events/news/2016/exclusive-breastfeeding/en/ https://www.familyeducation.com/life/benefits-breastfeeding/new-study-shows-breastfeeding-can-save-lives-money

She was even questioned by the police prior to being rescued - but because he made her wear a mask, nobody could tell it was her. Put a hat and a mask on child, and they look no different than the 2000 other kids around them. column31: Truth: In the first couple of weeks, most babies need some help learning to latch properly, and many will latch a bit shallowly when they're tired. And, mama's breasts need a chance to get used to breastfeeding. A *small* amount of achiness is normal during this time, and it should go away after those first couple weeks. A *lot* of pain, or sharp pain that doesn't ease after a minute or two upon latching, is a sign that something is wrong, and that mama may need to reach out to a lactation consultant for support. If you're a new mama who's experiencing some of the normal achiness, we have a Breast Balm that can help. It's edible, baby-safe, and even helps fight thrush. column31: 👉 Antibacterial Soap = Disrupted Hormones 👉 Antibacterial Soap = Contributes to Antibiotic Resistance and Superbugs + Guys, the reason for much of the concern is the use of triclosan, the active ingredient in many antibacterial products. This chlorinated phenolic compound has been linked to disrupted hormonal activity in animals. + Estrogen dominance is a big contributor to the irritating and sometimes debilitating symptoms of perimenopause. Avoiding any chemicals that produce the tendency toward estrogen dominance is vital for every woman over 40 if she desires a symptom free transition to menopause. It is also very possible that widespread use of this chemical (along with others like BPA) is a factor in the early puberty experienced by so many young girls today. In boys, estrogen mimickers produce the opposite effect. *I see this often on my clients reports while I'm bioscan testing them. + Obese boys, in particular, are at risk for delayed puberty, likely due to the estrogenic effects of the extra fat they are carrying combined with environmental exposure to estrogen mimickers like triclosan. Exposure to this chemical clearly has risks for anyone no matter what his/her age. Another disturbing finding is that triclosan has been shown to reduce circulating thyroxine (T4 – thyroid hormone) in rats. + Lack of sufficient circulating thyroid hormone produces the symptoms of hypothyroidism, currently at epidemic proportions in the Western world. You know the symptoms of hypothyroidism well – fatigue, thinning hair, depression, cold hands and feet, and difficulty losing weight. + Chances are you or someone in your household already suffers from it even if not yet diagnosed by a physician. Watch out, as triclosan is used not only in soap, but also detergents, cosmetics, deodorant, toothpaste, children’s clothing, and even toys. *This is why I use Young Living products and oils in my home, they are health SUPPORTING and are completely clean of any chemicals. #easybutton 🦠 Check out my article for an easy DIY antiviral & antibacterial hand wash safe for even sensitive skin ➜ http://www.integrativenutritionaltherapies.com/homemade-antiviral-foaming-hand-soap/

column31: P A E L L A & gazpacho 😍 Part of my family tree hails from Spain, where these two traditional dishes reign. 🇪🇸 Paella valenciana is something of an explosion of flavors, w/ tons of seafood like mussels, calamari, & shrimp on a bed of rice & tomatoes. Gazpacho is a smooth, cool summer soup made with a base of tomatoes, cucumbers & peppers. 🥣 To take ours over the top, we used all wild-caught & organic ingredients (natch) & used nourishing bone broth instead of water for the rice in the paella. Ahhhh. Deeply satisfying & delish.😋 Do you make any dishes that are a part of your family’s cultural traditions or heritage? And would you like the recipe for these two? ☀️ ☀️ ☀️ Paella y gazpacho. 😍 Son platos tradicionales de mis abuelos, bisabuelos, tatarabuelos etc. 🇪🇸 La paella está hecho con amor, caldo de hueso, y puros ingredientes orgánicos y sostenibles, incluyendo todos los mariscos. El gazpacho fue preparado con tomates frescos del mercado, con cebolla, pepino, ajo, y ají. Salió todo un sueño. 😇 Qué platos preparas tú que son tradicionales de tu pueblo o gente? column31: Translation: You are stupid. Just do whatever the "experts" tell you. But there's a big problem with this. When it comes to some scientific issues (like this author's field, astrophysics), the day-to-day knowledge doesn't affect us. Outside of enthusiasts, we *do* leave it to the experts. Health, on the other hand, is very personal. It's literally the care of our own bodies. If we listen to the "experts," and they turn out to be wrong, *we* are the ones who suffer the consequences. Who may live with damage for the rest of our lives. We can't abdicate our responsibility for ourselves. We can't wait for the experts to figure it out, or go against our own instincts and do something that feels very wrong. We may never be experts on ALL the knowledge that is out there on a health topic, but we are experts on our own bodies. Health science should not be elevated to the same level as, say, astrophysics. It's too personal It's too varied. People should never be encouraged to abandon all sense of reason and allow others to decide something so fundamental for them.
